cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper focuses on improving skip connections used in segmentation networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image segmentation and object detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method for skip connections that involves learning and selecting the most discriminative channels and regions, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on different datasets, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
